verbose_text: MRI brain showed fulminant contrast enhancing ovoid lesions, both nodular and ring enhancing involving both cerebral hemispheres involving callososeptal interface, also including left infratentorial involving pons and medulla oblongata raising suspicion of severe demyelination disorders (eg, acute disseminated encephalomyelitis (ADEM) or MS), malignancy and neuroinfection.
